20a%20utopian%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-parents-afford-childcare-get-stable-jobs-gbi-ubi-2024-8%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGuaranteed%2520basic%2520income%2520helps%2520some%2Cand%2520discourage%2520participants%2520from%2520working.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUBI%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20gained%20traction%20as%20an%20idea%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20its%20universal%20nature%20is%20still%20a%20difficult%20political%20sell.%20However%2C%20to%20test%20out%20the%20idea%20on%20a%20more%20limited%20basis%2C%20many%20cities%20and%20states%20have%20piloted%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%20programs%2C%20which%20offer%20recurring%20cash%20payments%20to%20all%20individuals%20in%20a%20population%20regardless%20of%20their%20socioeconomic%20status.%20There%20are%20no%20restrictions%20on%20how%20the%20money%20is%20spent%2C%20and%20no%20repayment%20is%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-opposition-discriminatory-universal-basic-income-argument-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguaranteed%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20programs%20offer%20recurring%20cash%20payments%2C%20but%20participants%20only%20receive%20the%20money%20for%20a%20set%20period%20of%20time%20%E2%80%94%20often%20between%20one%20and%20five%20years.%20Guaranteed%20basic%20income%20programs%20have%20specific%20criteria%3A%20participants%20typically%20have%20a%20household%20income%20that%20falls%20near%20the%20federal%20poverty%20line%20or%20they%20fit%20into%20a%20certain%20demographic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20there%20have%20been%20more%20than%20100%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhich-states-cities-have-guaranteed-basic-income-programs-low-income-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplaces%20that%20have%20tried%20basic%20income%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20with%20cities%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flos-angeles-guaranteed-basic-income-pilot-ubi-partner-violence-employment-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELos%20Angeles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchicago-basic-income-helped-mother-rent-an-apartment-ubi-gbi2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChicago%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Denver%2C%20and%20Atlanta%20offering%20participants%20direct%20cash%20payments%2C%20no%20strings%20attached.%20Countries%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-kenya-helps-families-buy-food-savings-ubi-gbi-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKenya%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Finland%2C%20India%2C%20and%20Canada%20have%20also%20tried%20the%20model%20as%20an%20approach%20to%20reducing%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epoverty.%20Most%20of%20the%20basic%20income%20programs%20launched%20in%20the%20US%20and%20abroad%20are%20fixed%2C%20short-term%20pilots%2C%20making%20them%20GBI%20instead%20of%20UBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20participants%2C%20an%20extra%20%24500%20a%20month%20is%20what%20they%20need%20to%20afford%20rent%20and%20groceries.%20For%20others%2C%20it's%20the%20support%20they%20need%20to%20pay%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeorgia-basic-income-afford-rent-daycare-single-mom-ubi-gbi-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20necessary%20prescriptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20life%20was%20always%20just%20a%20couple%20hundred%20dollars%20short%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20grandmother%20who%20participated%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-antonio-ubi-guaranteed-basic-income-pay-housing-expenses-work-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESan%20Antonio%20basic%20income%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20first%20time%2C%20I%20can%20breathe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20many%20people%20find%20the%20idea%20of%20handing%20out%20money%20without%20strings%20questionable%2C%20or%20even%20just%20plain%20wrong.%20In%20fact%2C%20some%20US%20programs%20continue%20to%20face%20legal%20challenges%20and%20political%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20basic%20income%2C%20its%20history%2C%20its%20potential%20advantages%2C%20and%20possible%20downsides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fda0379f-e10e-4c89-89e7-8ee81444f604%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20universal%20basic%20income%20and%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-basic-income-emergency-cash-rent-homes-government-housing-aid-2024-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAnd%2520across%252031%2520pilot%2520basic%2Chas%2520helped%2520families%2520stay%2520housed.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBasic%20income%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20unique%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20existing%20social%20safety%20nets%20in%20the%20US.%20Participants%20have%20full%20agency%20over%20their%20spending%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20federal%20programs%20that%20provide%20money%20for%20specific%20categories%3A%20like%20SNAP%20for%20food%2C%20Medicaid%20for%20healthcare%2C%20and%20housing%20vouchers%20for%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGBI%20programs%20often%20target%20specific%20groups%20of%20people.%20Previous%20GBI%20pilots%20have%20served%20low-income%20parents%20with%20young%20children%2C%20pregnant%20people%2C%20or%20individuals%20experiencing%20homelessness%2C%20artists%2C%20and%20budding%20entrepreneurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGBI%20pilot%20leaders%20often%20partner%20with%20researchers%20to%20study%20how%20participants%20use%20their%20cash%20payments.%20The%20studies%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20based%20on%20quantitative%20data%20like%20housing%20outcomes%20and%20qualitative%20information%20like%20interviews%20with%20participants%20%E2%80%94%20provide%20insight%20into%20how%20the%20pilots%20help%20participants%20during%20and%20after%20their%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20wave%20of%20pilot%20programs%20in%20the%20US%20began%20in%202019%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstockton-basic-income-experiment-success-employment-wellbeing-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebasic%20income%20experiment%20in%20Stockton%2C%20California%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20led%20by%20then-Mayor%20Michael%20Tubbs.%20The%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%20program%20offered%20125%20low-income%20people%20%24500%20monthly%20for%20two%20years.%20The%20Stockton%20pilot%20is%20widely%20used%20as%20an%20example%20for%20basic%20income%20in%20other%20cities%20across%20the%20country%2C%20and%20Tubbs%20went%20on%20to%20create%20and%20lead%20the%20national%20organization%20Mayors%20for%20a%20Guaranteed%20Income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20cash%20payment%20model%20has%20gained%20modern%20momentum%2C%20it%20isn't%20new.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-basic-income-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20idea%20for%20UBI%3C%2Fa%3E%20goes%20back%20to%20at%20least%20the%201500s.%20Spanish%20humanist%20Juan%20Luis%20Vives%20called%20for%20everyone%20to%20be%20given%20food%20even%20if%20they'd%20gambled%20away%20their%20money%20in%20the%2016th%20century%2C%20while%20American%20revolutionary%20Thomas%20Paine%20proposed%20a%20national%20fund%20in%201797%20that%20would%20pay%20citizens%20annually%20after%20they%20turned%2021.%20Similarly%2C%20economist%20and%20free%20market%20leader%20Milton%20Friedman%2C%20called%20for%20a%20negative%20income%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201967%2C%20Martin%20Luther%20King%20Jr.%20also%20showed%20support%20for%20UBI.%20He%20said%20cash%20payments%20could%20be%20a%20way%20to%20address%20historical%20racial%20discrimination%20and%20temper%20widespread%20poverty%20and%20unemployment%20in%20the%20Black%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Stockton%20waterfront%20at%20sunset%5C%22%2