20Texas%20judge%20ruled%20the%20FTC%20exceeded%20its%20authority%20and%20called%20the%20rule%20arbitrary%20and%20capricious.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20rule%20was%20slated%20to%20take%20effect%20on%20September%204.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20judge%20has%20blocked%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission's%20regulation%20that%20would%20have%20canceled%20nearly%20all%20existing%20non-compete%20agreements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuesday's%20decision%20is%20a%20relief%20to%20employers%2C%20who%20continue%20to%20remain%20protected%20against%20employees%20quitting%20and%20working%20for%20direct%20competitors.%20The%20rule%20would%20have%20gone%20into%20effect%20on%20September%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20district%20judge%20Ada%20Brown%20in%20Dallas%20said%20that%20the%20FTC%20does%20not%20have%20the%20authority%20to%20stop%20competition%20by%20adopting%20such%20broad%20rules.%20She%20called%20the%20rule%20%26quot%3Bcapricious.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Court%20concludes%20that%20the%20FTC%20lacks%20statutory%20authority%20to%20promulgate%20the%20Non-Compete%20Rule%2C%20and%20that%20the%20Rule%20is%20arbitrary%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20wrote%20in%20the%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uschamber.com%2Ffinance%2Fantitrust%2Fu-s-chamber-to-sue-ftc-over-unlawful-power-grab-on-noncompete-agreements-ban%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUS%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20lobbies%20on%20behalf%20of%20businesses%2C%20hit%20hard%20against%20the%20new%20rule%20on%20the%20same%20day%20FTC%20announced%20its%20decision.%20It%20said%20that%20it%20intended%20to%20sue%20the%20FTC%20over%20what%20it%20called%20an%20%26quot%3Bunlawful%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bblatant%20power%20grab%26quot%3B%20amounting%20to%20government%20%26quot%3Boverreach.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrown%20had%20temporarily%20blocked%20the%20rule%20in%20July%20for%20a%20small%20number%20of%20employers%20while%20she%20considered%20a%20bid%20by%20the%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20to%20strike%20it%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrown%20wrote%20that%20even%20if%20FTC%20had%20the%20authority%20to%20adopt%20the%20rule%2C%20it%20had%20not%20made%20a%20case%20for%20banning%20virtually%20all%20non-compete%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fban-noncompete-agreements-approved-ftc-challenges-await-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFTC%20voted%20to%20approve%20a%20nationwide%20ban%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20noncompete%20agreements%2C%20which%20apply%20to%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20roles%2C%20including%20white-collar%20roles%20and%20hourly%20wage%20jobs%20such%20as%20retail%20sales%20staff%20and%20food%20preparation%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNoncompete%20clauses%20keep%20wages%20low%2C%20suppress%20new%20ideas%2C%20and%20rob%20the%20American%20economy%20of%20dynamism%2C%20including%20from%20the%20more%20than%208%2C500%20new%20startups%20that%20would%20be%20created%20a%20year%20once%20noncompetes%20are%20banned%2C%26quot%3B%20Lina%20Khan%2C%20the%20FTC%20chair%2C%20said%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENoncompetes%20prohibit%20employees%20from%20working%20at%20competing%20companies%20even%20after%20they%20leave%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FTC%20says%20these%20%26quot%3Bexploitative%26quot%3B%20practices%20affect%20about%2030%20million%20workers%2C%20often%20forcing%20them%20to%20stay%20in%20jobs%20they%20hate%2C%20relocate%20when%20they%20don't%20want%20to%2C%20move%20to%20lower-paying%20fields%2C%20leave%20the%20workforce%20altogether%2C%20or%20face%20expensive%20litigation.%20The%20move%20could%20help%20American%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-wants-ban-noncompete-agreements-workers-make-300-billion-more-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20%24300%20billion%20more%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20FTC%20has%2