22_blank%5C%22%3Erammed%20earth%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20that%20is%20moulded%20into%20the%20desired%20shape.%20For%20the%20residence%20in%20question%2C%20Rane%20says%20the%20soil%20was%20procured%20from%20a%2060%20cm%20depth%20and%20cleaned%20using%20a%20mechanised%20sieve%20to%20remove%20organic%20matter%20like%20roots%20and%20stones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20recent%20past%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20collective%20push%20encouraging%20the%20use%20of%20the%20material.%20Rane%20cites%20its%20abundance%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20this%20push.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20most%20cases%2C%20it%20is%20available%20on-site%20making%20this%20one%20of%20the%20most%20sustainable%20methods%20of%20construction%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%20The%20fact%20that%20it%20leaves%20no%20debris%20behind%20is%20another%20boon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20architects%20are%20often%20complimented%20on%20the%20timeless%20charm%20that%20the%20residence%20exudes.%20They%20credit%20the%20walls%20for%20this.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20are%20breathable%20and%20porous%20because%20of%20the%20rammed%20earth%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rane%20points%20out.%20He%20adds%20that%20this%20quality%20also%20helps%20the%20home%20regulate%20its%20temperature%20and%20humidity%20levels.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20March%202023%20research%20study%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EScience%20Direct%20%3C%2Fem%3Ealigns%20with%20what%20the%20architects%20claim.%20Underlining%20the%20advantages%20of%20using%20rammed%20earth%2C%20like%20the%20decrease%20in%20the%20environmental%20and%20economic%20costs%20related%20to%20transportation%2C%20the%20reduction%20in%20industrial%20processing%20required%2C%20and%20the%20material%E2%80%99s%20thermal-mass%20technology%2C%20the%20article%20is%20a%20nod%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F225624%2Fmumbai-architect-sustainable-homes-mud-cool-summer-ecofriendly-design-ang136%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ematerial%E2%80%99s%20sustainable%20quotient%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArchitects%2C%20take%20notes%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Having%20worked%20with%20rammed%20earth%20for%20multiple%20projects%2C%20Rane%20cautions%20architects%20who%20are%20planning%20on%20doing%20the%20same.%20%E2%80%9CPay%20attention%20to%20the%20soil%20composition%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20varies%20at%20different%20locations%20at%20the%20same%20site%3B%20the%20proportion%20of%20soil%20mix%20needs%20to%20be%20adjusted%20accordingly.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20roof%20overhangs%20should%20be%20installed%20around%20the%20homes%20made%20out%20of%20rammed%20earth%2C%20particularly%20those%20located%20in%20rainfall-prone%20regions.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20walls%20made%20of%20rammed%20earth%20need%20protection%20from%20the%20rain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Timber%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20team%20at%20SJK%20Architects%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Mumbai-based%20architectural%20firm%20that%20has%20spent%20the%20last%20three%20decades%20designing%20spaces%20%E2%80%94%20was%20approached%20with%20an%20ask%20to%20design%20a%20retirement%20home%20and%20skill%20centre%20in%20Awas%2C%20Alibaug%2C%20they%20were%20keen%20on%20it%20having%20a%20sustainable%20touch.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETimber%20was%20the%20choice%20of%20material%20but%20not%20in%20its%20raw%20form.%20The%20architects%20decided%20to%20use%20Glue-Laminated%20Timber%20(GLT)%20and%20Cross-Laminated%20Timber%20(CLT)%20for%20the%20construction.%20These%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F231673%2Fmumbai-sustainable-home-no-air-conditioning-traditional-technique-palmyra-wood-ser106%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20engineered%20woods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20say%2C%20see%20multiple%20layers%20of%20timber%20bonded%20together%20with%20durable%2C%20moisture-resistant%20structural%20adhesives.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbout%20the%20material%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20What%20separates%20GLT%20from%20CLT%20is%20that%20in%20the%20former%2C%20laminates%20of%20structural%20timber%20are%20layered%20and%20glued%20in%20the%20same%20direction%2C%20on%20top%20of%20each%20other%2C%20while%20in%20CLT%2C%20each%20layer%20of%20timber%20is%20glued%20at%2090%20degrees%20to%20the%20layer%20above%20and%20below.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-1-1723551227.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20house%20at%20Awas%20in%20Alibaug%20was%20built%20using%20pre-engineered%20technology%20and%20timber%2C%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-1-1723551227.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-1-1723551227-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-1-1723551227-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-1-1723551227-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-1-1723551227-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-361161%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20house%20at%20Awas%20in%20Alibaug%20was%20built%20using%20pre-engineered%20technology%20and%20timber%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20SJK%20Architects%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20timber%20is%20wood%2C%20you%20point%20out.%20Is%20building%20with%20it%20sustainable%3F%20Sarika%20Shetty%2C%20one%20of%20the%20architects%20involved%20in%20the%20project%20responds%20by%20saying%20that%20this%20is%20where%20procurement%20comes%20into%20play.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20crucial%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20timber%20is%20sourced%20from%20certified%2C%20sustainably%20managed%20forests%2C%20even%20if%20it%20means%20sourcing%20from%20abroad.%20Utilising%20sea%20travel%20for%20transportation%20can%20significantly%20reduce%20emissions%20compared%20to%20air%20freight%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20research%20paper%20published%20in%202023%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F198111%2Fchennai-architect-sustainable-home-eco-friendly-construction-waste-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvantages%20of%20timber%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20assessed%20in%20comparison%20to%20its%20counterpart%20materials%20such%20as%20steel%20and%20concrete.%20The%20findings%20concluded%20that%20timber%20produces%20lower%20carbon%20emissions%20and%20has%20a%20lower%20environmental%20impact%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20other%20materials.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20architects%20agree.%20Elaborating%20on%20the%20use%20of%20CLT%20and%20GLT%2C%20they%20share%20that%20these%20are%20carbon-negative%20(emit%20less%20than%20zero%20CO2%20equivalents)%20and%20thus%20renewable%2C%20provided%20the%20timber%20is%20sourced%20from%20sustainably%20managed%20forests.%20It%20is%20tolerant%20to%20warping%20and%20cracking%2C%20making%20it%20an%20excellent%20choice%20of%20material.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShetty%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20seen%20that%20CLT%20buildings%20have%20less%20than%20half%20of%20the%20embodied%20CO2%20of%20conventional%20reinforced%20concrete%20buildings.%E2%80%9D%20Their%20light%20weight%2C%20she%20says%2C%20reduces%20the%20foundations%E2%80%99%20overall%20weight%20and%20allows%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F309050%2Farchitect-quits-job-to-build-sustainable-earth-mud-homes-across-south-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeasier%20construction%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20handling%20and%20transportation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20perk%20is%20that%20CLT%20and%20GLT%20are%20made%20from%20softwoods.%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20they%20can%20be%20impregnated%20with%20chemicals%20to%20make%20the%20timber%20termite-proof%2C%20an%20advantage%20not%20typically%20found%20with%20hardwoods%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Shetty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArchitects%2C%20take%20notes%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Shetty%20encourages%20architects%20to%20go%20in%20for%20species%20such%20as%20Douglas%20Fir%20and%20spruce%20pine%20fir%20which%20offer%20a%20lightweight%20alternative%20to%20traditional%20Indian%20hardwoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E3.%20Ventilated%20terracotta%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPicture%20a%20construction%20material%20that%20keeps%20the%20structure%20cool%20in%20the%20peak%20of%20Indian%20summers%2C%20provides%20acoustic%20insulation%20(cuts%20noise%20levels%20by%20up%20to%2015%20percent)%20and%20looks%20pretty!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArchitects%20of%20firm%20GPM%20Architects%20and%20Planners%20were%20as%20amazed%20as%20you%20are%20when%20they%20worked%20with%20ventilated%20terracotta%20tiles%20to%20design%20the%20Defence%20Office%20complexes%20in%20KG%20Marg%20and%20Africa%20Avenue%2C%20Delhi.%20If%20you%20pass%20by%2C%20you%E2%80%99ll%20agree.%20The%20campus%20makes%20for%20a%20beautiful%20tapestry%20with%20the%20terracotta%20tiles%20stealing%20the%20limelight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20how%20the%209.60%20lakh%20sq%20ft%20area%20was%20completed%20in%2010%20months%20using%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F271590%2Fman-builds-low-cost-ecofriendly-home-from-village-scrap-waste%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epre-engineered%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20architects%20say%20the%20terracotta%20made%20it%20easy.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1723551495.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ventilated%20terracotta%20makes%20for%20a%20great%20material%20that%20provides%20thermal%20and%20acoustic%20insulation%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1723551495.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1723551495-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1723551495-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1723551495-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2Fsustainable-architecture-2-1723551495-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-361163%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EVentilated%20terracotta%20makes%20for%20a%20great%20material%20that%20provides%20thermal%20and%20acoustic%20insulation%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20GPM%20Architects%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20you%20know%20the%20material%E2%80%99s%20use%20traces%20back%20to%20the%20Harappan%20Civilisation%20(3300-1300%20BC)%3F%20A%202024%20research%20study%20published%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EInternational%20Journal%20of%20Novel%20Research%20and%20Development%3C%2Fem%3E%20highlighted%20the%20eco-benefits%20of%20terracotta%20pointing%20to%20its%20energy%20efficiency.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20firing%20process%20used%20in%20terracotta%20production%20typically%20requires%20lower%2